Spec 074 Phase A — citizen roster, first-person view, research and the plumbing

The colony designs itself, and now the citizens have a place to live in
the engine as named, registered people instead of nameless capsules.

Research docs/research/2026-06-02-citizen-as-bot.md lays out the full
architecture for the operator's directive — one real Hermes pod per
resident, spawned via kooker-bot-spawner into a DMZ namespace called
citylife-citizens with egress allowed only to kooker-service-ai and the
citylife backend, with city documentation mounted, and each citizen
backed by a kooker-user with role CITYLIFE_CITIZEN. Skoonveld is the
reference pattern.

Spec 074 docs/specs/proposed/074-citizen-avatar-bot.md formalises this
as the next slice in BOTH queues (the external mirror at
D:\infra\projects\citylife-specs\proposed\ too).

This commit ships Phase A — the engine-side plumbing.

src/colony/bot/citizenRoster.ts — CitizenRoster, public-safe Citizen
records (the gateway URL never reaches the HUD, only the kooker user),
register/forHousehold/byId/setBotGatewayUrl/setTelegramHandle/
recordTokens. Every shown string passes through the existing
isPublicSafe denylist.

src/colony/bot/firstPersonView.ts — pure-engine FirstPersonView the
governor loop can read every tick. What the citizen sees of their
ground, the nearest road, up to four neighbours, three nearest buildings
plus three nearest civic anchors, the clock and the colony's mood. The
costly PNG counterpart will land in the renderer as a separate slice.

runtime.ts wires both — when the Border Patrol bot approves a household
and allocates a plot, the lead is registered on the roster. uiState.
citizens exposes the public slice so the HUD can show it. rt.
firstPersonView returns the live view of any citizen.

ColonyApp HUD adds a Citizens row showing awake-over-count and the
first two named residents.

Tests — bot.citizenRoster.test.ts and bot.firstPerson.test.ts. 474
tests pass, was 459. Typecheck clean.

The kooker-user mint, the spawner provision and the NetworkPolicy DMZ
land as their own PRs in their own repos, joekookerbot merges — those
briefs are next.

